"""Generate PER_ROW_EVIDENCE_MANIFEST.csv for the SBsql Surface-to-SBLR execution_plan.

Inputs (repo-local, no network):
  public_input_snapshot
  project/tests/sbsql_parser_worker/fixtures/surface_to_sblr/artifacts/STRICT_ROW_COVERAGE_LEDGER.csv
  project/tests/sbsql_parser_worker/fixtures/surface_to_sblr/artifacts/FUNCTION_SEMANTIC_ORACLE_MATRIX.csv
  project/tests/sbsql_parser_worker/fixtures/surface_to_sblr/artifacts/AUTHENTICATED_FULL_ROUTE_MATRIX.csv
  project/tests/sbsql_parser_worker/fixtures/surface_to_sblr/artifacts/SBLR_BINARY_ROUND_TRIP_MATRIX.csv

Output:
  project/tests/sbsql_parser_worker/fixtures/surface_to_sblr/artifacts/PER_ROW_EVIDENCE_MANIFEST.csv

For every SBsql surface row in the canonical registry, this generator
records the per-row evidence required by SBSFC-009A acceptance: final
state, CTest label, fixture path, implementation references, diagnostic
proof, and result proof. The manifest is the row-level closure record
that gates whether a row may be declared `e2e_passed`,
`exact_refusal_passed`, `cluster_provider_route_passed`, or
`private_profile_implemented`.

Baseline: every row's `final_state` is `pending` and proof fields carry
the canonical reference (oracle binding when known, refusal diagnostic
when status drives refusal, or `pending_row_level`/`pending_canonical_authority_entry`
when downstream slices must still produce evidence). As later slices land
row-level fixtures and CTest runs report passes, the manifest is updated
per row to record evidence collected, fixture results, and final state.

Architecture invariant compliance: read-only CSV consumption; no
transaction model touched; no engine, parser worker, server, listener,
storage, or MGA file modified; no WAL surface introduced. The manifest
records evidence requirements only.
"""

from __future__ import annotations

